AN ACT relating to mental health; requiring the Department of Health and Human
Services to create a pilot program to [study] collect and analyze data
on transcranial magnetic stimulation and electromagnetic brain
pulse treatment [;] under certain circumstances; and providing other
matters properly relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 [This] To the extent money is available, and with the use of existing personnel and
2 resources, this bill requires the Department of Health and Human Services to create a pilot
3 program to [study] collect and analyze data that is publicly available or voluntarily
4 provided to the pilot program related to best practices for, and the outcome of studies
5 concerning, transcranial magnetic stimulation and electromagnetic brain pulse treatment.
6 [Specifically, this bill requires: (1) the pilot program to study best practices, compile relevant
7 data, analyze risks and examine barriers associated with electromagnetic brain pulse
8 treatment; and (2)] This bill requires the Department to [submit] compile a report of [its] the
