THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. 1. The Department of Health and Human Services shall , to the
2 extent money is available, create a pilot program to [study electromagnetic brain
3 pulse treatment.
4 2. The pilot program must include, without limitation:] collect and analyze
5 data that is publicly available or voluntarily provided to the pilot program
6 concerning:
7 (a) The [identification of] best practices for transcranial magnetic
8 stimulation and electromagnetic brain pulse treatment [, including the
9 circumstances in which the treatment is safe and effective for patients;] ; and
10 (b) [An analysis of any risks to patients associated with electromagnetic brain
11 pulse treatment;
12 (c)] The [examination of data from publicly available] results of studies [or
13 reports] concerning transcranial magnetic stimulation and electromagnetic brain
14 pulse treatment . [; and
15 (d) An analysis of any barriers to the introduction or inclusion of
16 electromagnetic brain pulse treatment in medical practices in this State.]
17 2. The data described in subsection 1 may be collected from:
18 (a) Entities that provide transcranial magnetic stimulation or
19 electromagnetic brain pulse treatment in this State; and
20 (b) Public or private research institutions that conduct studies on
21 transcranial magnetic stimulation or electromagnetic brain pulse treatment
22 for persons with a substance use disorder, post-traumatic stress disorder or an
23 addictive disorder related to gambling.
24 3. The Department [may contract with persons and public or private entities
25 that are qualified] shall use existing personnel, resources and technology to
26 administer the pilot program.
27 4. The Department shall, on or before July 1, 2027, [submit] compile a report
28 of its findings and recommendations resulting from the pilot program [to :] , which
29 must be:
30 (a) [The Governor;] Posted on an Internet website maintained by the
31 Department; and
32 (b) [The] Submitted to the Director of the Legislative Counsel Bureau for
33 transmittal to the Joint Interim Standing Committee on Health and Human Services.
34 5. The Department may apply for and accept gifts, grants and donations to
35 assist with the implementation of the pilot program.
36 6. As used in this section [, “electromagnetic] :
37 (a) “Electromagnetic brain pulse treatment” means a noninvasive and non-
38 pharmaceutical treatment that uses an electroencephalograph and transcranial
39 magnetic stimulation to image and identify abnormal brainwaves and provide
40 treatment through the delivery of pulse-matching, electromagnetic stimulation
41 intended to restore normal brain function.
42 (b) “Transcranial magnetic stimulation” means a noninvasive procedure
43 that uses magnetic pulses to stimulate and alter brain activity.
44 Sec. 2. This act becomes effective on October 1, 2025, and expires by
45 limitation on September 30, 2027.

